 they live, to be recognized in their difference and at the same time integrated in the European national and supranational institutions.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aReligions. Mythology. Rationalism. 7aRELIGION / Religion, Politics & State.2bisacsh  aChristianity, European Union, Identity, Integration, Islam, Multiculturalism, Muslims, Religion.1 aBerger, Peter L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCasanova, José, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGöle, Nilüfer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHervieu-Léger, Danièle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartin, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMichalski, Krzysztof, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aModood, Tariq, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParekh, Bhikhu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoy, Olivier, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTaylor, Charles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCentral European University Press eBook-Package 2013-1998z978311078055040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9786155053900423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9786155053900/original  a978-3-11-078055-0  Central European University Press eBook-Package 2013-1998c1998d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles